\Sreplace one colour with another.
Click \s in the sprite \w and the selected pixel (and adjacent or all of the same colour) will be replaced with the current paint colour.
\Spaint outline circles.
To paint each circle, click \s at its centre and then at a point on the edge.
\Spaint ellipse outlines.
To paint each ellipse, click \s at its centre, at a point that gives the width at the centre, and at a point on the edge.
\Spaint circular arcs.
To paint each arc click \s at the circle centre, and at the start and end of the arc.
\Spaint text, using the system font.
Enter the desired text in the writable icon that appears when this tool is selected, then click \s in a sprite \w to paint the text.
\Spaint filled circles.
To paint each circle, click \s at its centre and then at a point on the edge.
\Spaint filled ellipses.
To paint each ellipse, click \s at its centre, at a point that gives the width at the centre, and at a point on the edge.
\Spaint circle segments.
To paint each segment click \s at the circle centre, and at the start and end of the segment.
\Spaint circle sectors.
To paint each sector click \s at the circle centre, and at the start and end of the sector.
